headline: John Rich welcomes 'The Five' to Nashville
subHeadline: 'The Five' broadcasts live from the Wildhorse Saloon in downtown Nashville.

utterances.speaker: DANA PERINO, CO-HOST
utterances.sentences: Hello, everyone. I'm Dana Perino along with Greg Gutfeld, John Rich, Donna Brazile, and Jesse Watters. It's 5 o'clock in New York City, 4' o'clock here in Nashville, Tennessee, and this is "The Five."

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.sentences: All right. Welcome to Nashville. We are so excited to be here at the Wild Horse Saloon in downtown music city. We have an amazing crowd here for our big show and country music superstar John Rich cohosting with us for the hour. He took us around Nashville for a special tour, board his red neck, the party bus, and that is coming up later. You're not going to miss that.  Plus, we have a very special guest. Kathie Lee Gifford will be joining us on set. And we're also happy to have the Joe Denim Band perform. Honestly, can we just move here? John Rich, thanks for having us in your city.

utterances.speaker: JOHN RICH, GUEST CO-HOST
utterances.sentences: Welcome to Nashville. It's a pleasure to have you guys. This is how it feels in Nashville all the time. Loud country music, everybody is having a great time. A bunch of patriots all getting together just celebrating the American dream. Can I get a hell yeah?

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.sentences: Donna Brazile, you had your 40th birthday in this bar.

utterances.speaker: DONNA BRAZILE, GUEST CO-HOST
utterances.sentences: I -- you wouldn't believe this because I know I just look a day pass 25, but I celebrated my 40th birthday here in the city of Nashville right here at the Wild Horse Saloon. I am back. Thank you, Nashville.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.sentences: Jesse Watters, you and I were here last year for the charity celebrity -- the celebrity waiter event.

utterances.speaker: JESSE WATTERS, CO-HOST
utterances.sentences: Yeah. It's good to be back in Nashville. I forgot Nashville was Watters' World.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.sentences: I think it feels like Gutfeld country, too.

utterances.speaker: GREG GUTFELD, CO-HOST
utterances.sentences: Yes, yes, yes, yes, yes. Reminds me a lot of Berkeley.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.sentences: Oh, yeah.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: It's like the opposite of Berkeley. It's Berkeley's evil twin. I just think it's unfair that we're the only people in this bar who doesn't have a drink.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.sentences: Yeah.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: Four of us don't have a drink.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.sentences: We'll let you guess who that is. All right, we have a lot of fun in store, but first we're going to get some political news. Bernie Sanders defending his socialist agenda during last night's Fox News town hall. The 2020 front runner getting combative after releasing his tax returns that showed he's a millionaire. Watch.

utterances.speaker: BRET BAIER, FOX NEWS
utterances.sentences: Your taxes do show that you're a millionaire. You did make a million in 2016, 2017. Your right at the top 61 in 2018, but your marginal tax rate was 26 percent because of President Trump's tax cuts. So why not say, you know, I'm leading this revolution. I'm not going to take those.

utterances.speaker: SEN. BERNIE SANDERS, D-VT.
utterances.sentences: Come on. I am -- I pay the taxes that I owe.

utterances.speaker: MARTHA MACCALLUM, FOX NEWS
utterances.sentences: Would you be willing to pay 52 percent on the money that you made. You can volunteer. You can send it back.

utterances.speaker: SANDERS
utterances.sentences: You can volunteer, too. We have a --

utterances.speaker: MACCALLUM
utterances.sentences: But you suggested -- you suggested everybody in your bracket should do.

utterances.speaker: SANDERS
utterances.sentences: Martha, why don't you give? You made more money than I do.

utterances.speaker: MACCALLUM
utterances.sentences: I didn't suggest a wealth tax.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.sentences: Also, Sanders said he never disparaged millionaires.

utterances.speaker: BAIER
utterances.sentences: You do spend a lot of time vilifying millionaires.

utterances.speaker: SANDERS
utterances.sentences: Oh, I don't vilify. It's not vilifying. To say that people have a whole lot of money, in some cases billions of dollars of wealth, they should pay their fair share of taxes.

utterances.speaker: BAIER
utterances.sentences: Right --

utterances.speaker: SANDERS
utterances.sentences: That's not vilifying.

utterances.speaker: BAIER
utterances.sentences: last question on this. A lot of millionaires and billionaires give a ton to charity. You gave 3.4 percent.

utterances.speaker: SANDERS
utterances.sentences: My wife and I do give money to charity, all right. And we're proud to do what we did.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.sentences: And Sanders admitting that taxes will go up under his Medicare for all plan.

utterances.speaker: SANDERS
utterances.sentences: Health care is not free --

utterances.speaker: MACCALLUM
utterances.sentences: Of course not.

utterances.speaker: SANDERS
utterances.sentences: -- suggest that we're going to --

utterances.speaker: MACCALLUM
utterances.sentences: You just said it was going to be free for everyone.

utterances.speaker: SANDERS
utterances.sentences: It's going to be free at the point of when you use it, OK? If you go -- why are you so shock by this? Are people going to pay more in taxes, yes. But at the end of the day the overwhelming majority of people are going to end up paying less for health care.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.sentences: So the talk of the town -- well, not just the town but the country, one of the reasons, of course, we wanted to get out of Nashville - - New York City, get out of our bubble, come here and see all of you wonderful people here and talk about this. He's talking about a fundamental change in America and the way that we do government in this country, and business and capitalism. Your thoughts, Jesse.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: Bernie Sanders is an ungrateful freeloader.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: Thank you, everybody.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: Quit while you're ahead.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: Listen, Bernie Sanders should be thanking the American taxpayer instead of trying to shake us down. He's never had a real job in his life. We pay his salary. We pay for his health care, his staff, his travel, his security. We pay for everything. And all he does is he goes around and makes promises he can't keep and he spends money that we can afford to spend.  Bernie Sanders has never saved anything. He's never budgeted anything. And when he became a millionaire, then he stopped attacking millionaires and started attacking billionaires. And the other thing is when he became a millionaire that first year, he didn't pay his fair share, he actually only paid 1 percent to charity, so he doesn't really put his money where his mouth is. And he doesn't have a health care plan. All he does is scream about Medicare for all. He doesn't say how the plan works or how he's going to pay for it. So I think a lot of people should be nervous on the Democrat side, if Bernie gets the nomination, you're going to have four more years of Donald Trump as president.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.sentences: Donna, you want to respond and then we'll get Greg in here.

utterances.speaker: BRAZILE
utterances.sentences: Well, as you all know, I am a quote-unquote unattached Democrat.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: Yes, ma'am.

utterances.speaker: BRAZILE
utterances.sentences: Is it OK if I touch you?

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: Yes, ma'am.

utterances.speaker: BRAZILE
utterances.sentences: I'm patting these brothers on the back.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: That's the Joe Biden rule.

utterances.speaker: BRAZILE
utterances.sentences: Yeah.

utterances.speaker: BRAZILE
utterances.sentences: No, it's the Joe Biden rule. You can touch me back.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: All right.

utterances.speaker: BRAZILE
utterances.sentences: First of all, I want to say that I thought Bernie did a great job. To be on the hot seat last night, I thought he got a very warm reception from the Fox audience. I also believed that he spelled out not just his plan on Medicare for all, which is a plan that is supported by millions of Americans, but he also talked about his vision for the country. His vision, I think, is in the mainstream. He wants to make sure that we have a living wage. He wants to make sure that children have access to college. And yes, I have to tell you, Jesse, because I read it, he has a plans to pay for everything that he has proposed.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: He has a plan and it's just to raise taxes. That's not a plan.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.sentences: Let me get Greg on here. You can -- of course you can comment on the specifics. But I also wonder about his approach. He doesn't care if he's like. He is not going to apologize. He's just Bernie.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: You know what I like about it, you know when we're playing the tape with the sound off if your watching, we have -- he's talking -- he looks like somebody at the counter complaining about the tuna fish salad.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: It would have been great to show the tape when I said that, but it's OK. Look, I like that part where he got angry. He got angry when they asked him about his success. That's what it's like to be an American, all right? It's when somebody questions your success as though somehow you don't deserve it. At that moment Bernie Sanders went from a socialist to an individual who prides his liberty and that was actually gratifying. That would never have happened on MSNBC or anywhere else. The real problem here is that we -- every five years, we have to inoculate against socialism because it's not taught in the universities. Basically, capitalism is like a vaccine against the disease of socialism. It eradicates socialism, so you forget that it's there and then it comes back, just like the measles. Just like the measles.  So what you need -- capitalism actually enables socialism to exist, just like a vaccine allows people not to take the vaccine.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.sentences: John Rich, back in the -- we call it the green room, which wasn't really green but it was a lot of fun. We were talking about your perspective on this and how you were raised and how you don't want anyone telling you what you can't achieve.

utterances.speaker: RICH
utterances.sentences: Correct. So I was raised by a dad who's a preacher and that was his passion. He wasn't going to make a bunch of money being a preacher but he was called to be a preacher. And so, to fill in the gaps on actual bills that came in, my dad was willing to do any job there was. And I watched him be a night watchman at a bank in Amarillo, Texas. I watch him slug pugs. I watched him sell cars. I watched him give guitar lessons, anything he could do to make ends meet. And he did make ends meet.  And he told me, he said, son, I don't care if you're poor, in the middle, or if you're rich, always know that if you woke up in America today it's one of the best days of your life because people don't have the right to chase the American dream around the world. Work as hard as you want to, son, and dream as big as you can, and remember our constitution does not guarantee as happiness. It guarantees us a right to pursue happiness. And in the pursuit of happiness should make you happy that you got the right to go for it. That's what it's all about. That's how I go at it.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.sentences: All right, I agree. I agree, all right. As you can tell we're just getting started here in Nashville. We have a great show coming up. Kathie Lee Gifford joined us live on set. Plus, John Rich takes us around Music City on his red neck reverie party bus. But first, a Democratic congressman under fire for comparing Trump's presidency to the devastating Notre Dame fire. We'll be back.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: Welcome back to The Five live from Nashville, Tennessee. Democrats and the media are melting down ahead of the Mueller report being released on Thursday. Democratic Congressman Steve Cohen actually using the devastating Notre Dame fire to attack President Trump. Take a look.

utterances.speaker: REP. STEVE COHEN, D-TENN.
utterances.sentences: What this president has done, and what he's done to the constitution, what he's done with the people's respect for our government, what he's done to the constitution and the rule law is as bad as that fire did to Notre Dame.  He's torching the entire structure of government and the people's respect for it. He was not exonerated, says Mueller. Mueller knows more about that than Barr. Barr was a hit man. Barr was a hit man hired to do his job, he's doing his job.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: And the liberal media lashing out at President Trump and claiming A.G. Bill Barr is behind some sort of cover up.

utterances.speaker: UNIDENTIFIED MALE
utterances.sentences: He's panicking. It's a laughable freak out on Donald Trump's part. He's just spitting out everything he can.

utterances.speaker: UNIDENTIFIED FEMALE
utterances.sentences: A lot of people are on spring break. Congress is on recess. They're putting this release as late as possible before Easter weekend when they might get the least amount of attention.

utterances.speaker: UNIDENTIFIED MALE
utterances.sentences: You've got to wonder why he's doing all of this. What he's doing it now? Is it because he's got reason to fear what's coming?

utterances.speaker: UNIDENTIFIED MALE
utterances.sentences: Barr wants to use this process to try to play down the report heading into a Friday holiday weekend rather than play it up.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: Well, one of the reasons we wanted to get out of New York City and out of the city was to find out what other people across the country in the heart land are talking about and it's not about the Mueller report, Greg.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: No, they're talking about your hair.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: I swear if your hair got any higher, it would have its own altitude. I don't know what's going on. But you know what the funny thing is, OK, this Mueller freak out is because -- I guess the reports coming out on Thursday. It's like the media -- they're like drug addicts who found out there's a new cheaper drug on the street and they're getting the craving. They've got the Mueller craving. They should just quit cold turkey. The problem is they can't quit cold turkey because they sold their audience a bill of goods. They've made it sound like -- they made the Mueller report into the Game of Thrones, right? But it turns out it's going to be like Bobby Ewing's dream. You wake up, nothing's gonna be there, and what are they gonna tell their viewers which are hemorrhaging, CNN losing viewers because they lied to them about this.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: Yeah. It looks like the audiences of CNN and MSNBC are hooked on fake news, as Greg says. They neither fix and they have to hear scandalous conspiratorial reports or they're not going to watch.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.sentences: Well, I think that's why you get the hyperbole, right? So you have the comparison to the burning of Notre Dame which was felt worldwide. It was like a gut punch where people watching that beautiful building, the place were so many religious experiences have been held over the years, including by young people who are sitting right here. So, obviously, it just gets to be a little bit over-the-top. And the thing is if you cry wolf that many times and then there's nothing, then you don't have anything to run on.

utterances.speaker: BRAZILE
utterances.sentences: No, I think everybody wants to see it. Look, this coming Friday, I have nothing to do. I don't have to cook. I ate this remarkable chicken here in Nashville. I'm on a crash diet. So I have the munchies and I'm waiting for the Mueller report. See --

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: Yes, I tell you.

utterances.speaker: BRAZILE
utterances.sentences: I've got the munchies, OK?

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: You've got the munchies.

utterances.speaker: BRAZILE
utterances.sentences: Four hundred and twenty members of Congress --

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: You've got the Mueller munchies.

utterances.speaker: BRAZILE
utterances.sentences: I've got the Mueller munchies.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: Yes.

utterances.speaker: BRAZILE
utterances.sentences: And I want to read it. I want to read it page by page. I hope there's pictures in it, Greg, because if there's pictures I read it faster. If you give me some liquor, I'll read it quicker.

utterances.speaker: RICH
utterances.sentences: Whoa.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: I miss that.

utterances.speaker: RICH
utterances.sentences: Welcome to Nashville.

utterances.speaker: BRAZILE
utterances.sentences: I've been hanging out with you guys all day, so I know what to expect. No, but seriously, this -- I'm glad it's coming out. I'm glad we get an opportunity to look at it. I'm glad we get an opportunity to finally say once and for all the country was under attack. We know what happened in 2016. And perhaps we can learn from the mistakes of 2016, and don't let them get repeated in 2020.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: We do know what happened in 2016. Trump won.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: John Rich.

utterances.speaker: BRAZILE
utterances.sentences: And we also know that Vladimir Putin wanted Trump to win. The question is --

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: OK. Let's get to John.

utterances.speaker: BRAZILE
utterances.sentences: I want to get to John because, you know, I'm enjoying him.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: OK.

utterances.speaker: BRAZILE
utterances.sentences: And he doesn't have to wear a hat to cover all of that hair. I want to see it because I do believe at the end of the day we as Americans must understand how to defend our country from future cyberattacks. That said, Brother John.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: OK.

utterances.speaker: RICH
utterances.sentences: Yes, ma'am.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: Take it away.

utterances.speaker: RICH
utterances.sentences: I think that -- that is not what your average everyday American cares about. That's what I think. I think they care about what their tax rate is. I think they care about, did they get their job back or keep the job they had. And if they did, did their wages go up? That's what I think -- you go back to the Bernie Sanders piece how he sell all these books. How do you think people have money to buy all his books? They got their taxes reduced.

utterances.speaker: RICH
utterances.sentences: Whether they know that or not, that's what happened. And so, you know, I grew up in a double wide trailer in Texas, nothing fancy, and I see all these stuff going on and I know that's how the multitude of Americans actually feel. They don't care about this report. This just a media thing that none of us really care about honestly.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: Jesse, you actually keep your hair in a double wide trailer.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: My hair is about as high as Colorado, isn't it?

utterances.speaker: RICH
utterances.sentences: Higher the hair, closer to God.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: That's right.

utterances.speaker: BRAZILE
utterances.sentences: But it's all legally your hair.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: Yes, all legal. That's all legal. Not edible, though.

utterances.speaker: RICH
utterances.sentences: I think we should let a good Nashville girl run their fingers through your hair before the show is over.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: All right.

utterances.speaker: RICH
utterances.sentences: Do we have any volunteers? Any volunteers? Come on down.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: I think that violates some human resources law. You're going to end up getting sued.

utterances.speaker: RICH
utterances.sentences: Not in Nashville.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.sentences: Well, here's what I think. This report when it comes out on Thursday, you will have breathless reporting. Like, take a moment -- I just find it very hard to believe that Bill Barr, the new attorney general who has this amazing track record in Washington, D.C., came out and said there's no collusion and basically nothing on obstruction. I find it very hard to believe that he wasn't being truthful. And so, now the media has built it up that he is a liar? I find that -- I think that they're going to have egg on their face again.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: All right. Donna, wipe the egg off in the break, all right? We'll be right back. We have a lot more coming up live from Nashville, including checking out some of the top spots on John Rich party bus. But first, President Trump says he's ready to send illegal immigrants to sanctuary cities.

utterances.speaker: BRAZILE
utterances.sentences: Welcome back to "The Five" live from Nashville. President Trump is attacking Democrats while he stands firm on his plans to send migrants to sanctuary cities.

utterances.speaker: PRESIDENT DONALD TRUMP
utterances.sentences: It would be a lot easier if Congress would get together and the Democrats would agree to get rid of these loopholes, these horrible and foolish loopholes, the catch and release, and chain migration, and visa lottery.

utterances.speaker: BRAZILE
utterances.sentences: You know, I think the president is on shaky legal ground. Some in his administration believe it as well. And you know members of Congress will oppose it. But some of the migrant, mayors and others are saying bring it on, Mr. President. What's your view, brother?

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: I take it you're referring to me, not Dana.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: This reminds me of when you -- when somebody brags about their gym routine, what they can lift, what they can squat, and then you asked them to help you move and suddenly they have a bad back.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: Greg, I have a bad back.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: There you have a bad back. But that's the liberal mayor. That's De Blasio saying, oh, this is -- wait, you want the migrants to come here and now you don't. Why is it, because of Trump. Put your money where your mouth is. It's only an opinion if you don't -- it's not an opinion if there's no practical belief behind it.

utterances.speaker: BRAZILE
utterances.sentences: These individuals have been caught at the border. There are not enough beds. And what the president is proposing out of retaliation because the Democrats are not going along with his plan, is to ship them off to cities, it's costly, on buses, vans, planes, airplanes, your private jet --

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: You don't want to have them walk.

utterances.speaker: BRAZILE
utterances.sentences: But this is the point. The point is, is that why not go to Congress if this is what the president believes?

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: Any -- that begins with why not go to Congress never end well.

utterances.speaker: BRAZILE
utterances.sentences: Well, the president had Republicans for two years and nothing happens.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: Donna, Democrats do with they usually do. They got caught with their pants down.

utterances.speaker: BRAZILE
utterances.sentences: Really?

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: Donald Trump called their bluff and now they're shaking in their boots. This is what happens. For the last two years, Democrats said there's no crisis. We don't need walls. We need bridges. The caravan is just a bunch of women and children. We need workers. Trump is trying to stir up hate and resentment. Then all of a sudden Trump said, OK, you take him then. And then what happened. They totally changed their rhetoric when they've got smacked in the face by reality. If that happened and they sent 30,000 refugees to midtown Manhattan, what do you think Bill de Blasio would do. He'd have a humanitarian crisis. He'd have a political crisis. He can't even handle a snow storm.

utterances.speaker: BRAZILE
utterances.sentences: But it seems as though the President is trying to throw everything against the wall to see what sticks and this is not going to stick.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.sentences: I think you know we talked a little bit about this yesterday. He's changing the debate, right. So, he hasn't been able to achieve some of the things to Congress because of Greg says that doesn't - that's not working well. I don't see why the Democrats instead of saying, well that's just - we can't have that. And now their claim for an investigation.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: Good impression.

utterances.speaker: BRAZILE
utterances.sentences: Yes.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.sentences: OK. Why don't they just flip the script and say and as President said, well you know that's never going to happen and sorry that you can't achieve anything and you're the worst deal maker ever. OK, whatever. And just sit back instead they have to make such a big deal about it and call for an investigation that--

utterances.speaker: BRAZILE
utterances.sentences: That's because the President continue - John you have a point.

utterances.speaker: RICH
utterances.sentences: Well. I was just going to say if you really care about the folks that are piling up on the border, do you want them to stay in an overcrowded border town or do you want to send them to Northern California in the upper level districts and zip codes of that state where they can really have a nice meal, nice place to--

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: I heard the wine in San Francisco is really good.

utterances.speaker: BRAZILE
utterances.sentences: Just so you all know sanctuary cities are all over the country not just in big cities, but also small and rural communities. No, it is true. I've studied this issue. The sanctuary cities are all across America. But you know what, I want to say this, I think it's time that Congress and the President get together and try to solve this immigration crisis.

utterances.speaker: RICH
utterances.sentences: I agree with this.

utterances.speaker: BRAZILE
utterances.sentences: All right. Now, by the way, Kathie Lee Gifford is here. Live here at Nashville. Kathie Lee, come on over.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: I think that song is about gambling. I'm not sure. Welcome back to The Five for Nashville. That's the Joe Denim band playing live music. Joining us now is TV legend. Don't you hate that? Call you a legend.

utterances.speaker: KATHIE LEE GIFFORD, TELEVISION HOST
utterances.sentences: I hate that. You're almost dead.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: You're not there though.

utterances.speaker: GIFFORD
utterances.sentences: No.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: You've got more lives than cats. Let's put it that way. I miss you.

utterances.speaker: GIFFORD
utterances.sentences: I miss you too buddy.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: What have you been up to?

utterances.speaker: GIFFORD
utterances.sentences: Not much.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: You used to talk a lot.

utterances.speaker: GIFFORD
utterances.sentences: Mommy again.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.sentences: Congratulations.

utterances.speaker: GIFFORD
utterances.sentences: I know. I'm thrilled about that. I knew that was coming. I just didn't know when it was going to happen.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.sentences: It's sort of a long walk up to the - because you announced quite a while ago that you were going to leave The Today Show. What's it been like in the last, was it 10 days or so?

utterances.speaker: GIFFORD
utterances.sentences: I think so I've lost - I mean--

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.sentences: You're not counting.

utterances.speaker: GIFFORD
utterances.sentences: I'm not counting because I had given my notice two years before because I knew it was time. You know you've run out of tick tock in life and there are things I wanted to do and been dying to do, and you've just got to make time for certain things. And I've been so blessed to be there for 11 years and make the friendships that I had. But it was time.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: Donna, you want to respond and then we'll get Greg in here.

utterances.speaker: BRAZILE
utterances.utterance: Well, as you all know, I am a quote-unquote unattached Democrat.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Yes, ma'am.

utterances.speaker: BRAZILE
utterances.utterance: Is it OK if I touch you?

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Yes, ma'am.

utterances.speaker: BRAZILE
utterances.utterance: I'm patting these brothers on the back.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: That's the Joe Biden rule.

utterances.speaker: BRAZILE
utterances.utterance: Yeah.

utterances.speaker: BRAZILE
utterances.utterance: No, it's the Joe Biden rule. You can touch me back.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: All right.

utterances.speaker: BRAZILE
utterances.utterance: First of all, I want to say that I thought Bernie did a great job. To be on the hot seat last night, I thought he got a very warm reception from the Fox audience. I also believed that he spelled out not just his plan on Medicare for all, which is a plan that is supported by millions of Americans, but he also talked about his vision for the country. His vision, I think, is in the mainstream. He wants to make sure that we have a living wage. He wants to make sure that children have access to college. And yes, I have to tell you, Jesse, because I read it, he has a plans to pay for everything that he has proposed.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: He has a plan and it's just to raise taxes. That's not a plan.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: Let me get Greg on here. You can -- of course you can comment on the specifics. But I also wonder about his approach. He doesn't care if he's like. He is not going to apologize. He's just Bernie.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: You know what I like about it, you know when we're playing the tape with the sound off if your watching, we have -- he's talking -- he looks like somebody at the counter complaining about the tuna fish salad.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: It would have been great to show the tape when I said that, but it's OK. Look, I like that part where he got angry. He got angry when they asked him about his success. That's what it's like to be an American, all right? It's when somebody questions your success as though somehow you don't deserve it. At that moment Bernie Sanders went from a socialist to an individual who prides his liberty and that was actually gratifying. That would never have happened on MSNBC or anywhere else. The real problem here is that we -- every five years, we have to inoculate against socialism because it's not taught in the universities. Basically, capitalism is like a vaccine against the disease of socialism. It eradicates socialism, so you forget that it's there and then it comes back, just like the measles. Just like the measles. So what you need -- capitalism actually enables socialism to exist, just like a vaccine allows people not to take the vaccine.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: John Rich, back in the -- we call it the green room, which wasn't really green but it was a lot of fun. We were talking about your perspective on this and how you were raised and how you don't want anyone telling you what you can't achieve.

utterances.speaker: RICH
utterances.utterance: Correct. So I was raised by a dad who's a preacher and that was his passion. He wasn't going to make a bunch of money being a preacher but he was called to be a preacher. And so, to fill in the gaps on actual bills that came in, my dad was willing to do any job there was. And I watched him be a night watchman at a bank in Amarillo, Texas. I watch him slug pugs. I watched him sell cars. I watched him give guitar lessons, anything he could do to make ends meet. And he did make ends meet. And he told me, he said, son, I don't care if you're poor, in the middle, or if you're rich, always know that if you woke up in America today it's one of the best days of your life because people don't have the right to chase the American dream around the world. Work as hard as you want to, son, and dream as big as you can, and remember our constitution does not guarantee as happiness. It guarantees us a right to pursue happiness. And in the pursuit of happiness should make you happy that you got the right to go for it. That's what it's all about. That's how I go at it.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: All right, I agree. I agree, all right. As you can tell we're just getting started here in Nashville. We have a great show coming up. Kathie Lee Gifford joined us live on set. Plus, John Rich takes us around Music City on his red neck reverie party bus. But first, a Democratic congressman under fire for comparing Trump's presidency to the devastating Notre Dame fire. We'll be back.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Welcome back to The Five live from Nashville, Tennessee. Democrats and the media are melting down ahead of the Mueller report being released on Thursday. Democratic Congressman Steve Cohen actually using the devastating Notre Dame fire to attack President Trump. Take a look.

utterances.speaker: REP. STEVE COHEN, D-TENN.
utterances.utterance: What this president has done, and what he's done to the constitution, what he's done with the people's respect for our government, what he's done to the constitution and the rule law is as bad as that fire did to Notre Dame. He's torching the entire structure of government and the people's respect for it. He was not exonerated, says Mueller. Mueller knows more about that than Barr. Barr was a hit man. Barr was a hit man hired to do his job, he's doing his job.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: And the liberal media lashing out at President Trump and claiming A.G. Bill Barr is behind some sort of cover up.

utterances.speaker: UNIDENTIFIED MALE
utterances.utterance: He's panicking. It's a laughable freak out on Donald Trump's part. He's just spitting out everything he can.

utterances.speaker: UNIDENTIFIED FEMALE
utterances.utterance: A lot of people are on spring break. Congress is on recess. They're putting this release as late as possible before Easter weekend when they might get the least amount of attention.

utterances.speaker: UNIDENTIFIED MALE
utterances.utterance: You've got to wonder why he's doing all of this. What he's doing it now? Is it because he's got reason to fear what's coming?

utterances.speaker: UNIDENTIFIED MALE
utterances.utterance: Barr wants to use this process to try to play down the report heading into a Friday holiday weekend rather than play it up.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Well, one of the reasons we wanted to get out of New York City and out of the city was to find out what other people across the country in the heart land are talking about and it's not about the Mueller report, Greg.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: No, they're talking about your hair.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: I swear if your hair got any higher, it would have its own altitude. I don't know what's going on. But you know what the funny thing is, OK, this Mueller freak out is because -- I guess the reports coming out on Thursday. It's like the media -- they're like drug addicts who found out there's a new cheaper drug on the street and they're getting the craving. They've got the Mueller craving. They should just quit cold turkey. The problem is they can't quit cold turkey because they sold their audience a bill of goods. They've made it sound like -- they made the Mueller report into the Game of Thrones, right? But it turns out it's going to be like Bobby Ewing's dream. You wake up, nothing's gonna be there, and what are they gonna tell their viewers which are hemorrhaging, CNN losing viewers because they lied to them about this.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Yeah. It looks like the audiences of CNN and MSNBC are hooked on fake news, as Greg says. They neither fix and they have to hear scandalous conspiratorial reports or they're not going to watch.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: Well, I think that's why you get the hyperbole, right? So you have the comparison to the burning of Notre Dame which was felt worldwide. It was like a gut punch where people watching that beautiful building, the place were so many religious experiences have been held over the years, including by young people who are sitting right here. So, obviously, it just gets to be a little bit over-the-top. And the thing is if you cry wolf that many times and then there's nothing, then you don't have anything to run on.

utterances.speaker: BRAZILE
utterances.utterance: No, I think everybody wants to see it. Look, this coming Friday, I have nothing to do. I don't have to cook. I ate this remarkable chicken here in Nashville. I'm on a crash diet. So I have the munchies and I'm waiting for the Mueller report. See --

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Yes, I tell you.

utterances.speaker: BRAZILE
utterances.utterance: I've got the munchies, OK?

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: You've got the munchies.

utterances.speaker: BRAZILE
utterances.utterance: Four hundred and twenty members of Congress --

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: You've got the Mueller munchies.

utterances.speaker: BRAZILE
utterances.utterance: I've got the Mueller munchies.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Yes.

utterances.speaker: BRAZILE
utterances.utterance: And I want to read it. I want to read it page by page. I hope there's pictures in it, Greg, because if there's pictures I read it faster. If you give me some liquor, I'll read it quicker.

utterances.speaker: RICH
utterances.utterance: Whoa.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: I miss that.

utterances.speaker: RICH
utterances.utterance: Welcome to Nashville.

utterances.speaker: BRAZILE
utterances.utterance: I've been hanging out with you guys all day, so I know what to expect. No, but seriously, this -- I'm glad it's coming out. I'm glad we get an opportunity to look at it. I'm glad we get an opportunity to finally say once and for all the country was under attack. We know what happened in 2016. And perhaps we can learn from the mistakes of 2016, and don't let them get repeated in 2020.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: We do know what happened in 2016. Trump won.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: John Rich.

utterances.speaker: BRAZILE
utterances.utterance: And we also know that Vladimir Putin wanted Trump to win. The question is --

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: OK. Let's get to John.

utterances.speaker: BRAZILE
utterances.utterance: I want to get to John because, you know, I'm enjoying him.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: OK.

utterances.speaker: BRAZILE
utterances.utterance: And he doesn't have to wear a hat to cover all of that hair. I want to see it because I do believe at the end of the day we as Americans must understand how to defend our country from future cyberattacks. That said, Brother John.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: OK.

utterances.speaker: RICH
utterances.utterance: Yes, ma'am.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Take it away.

utterances.speaker: RICH
utterances.utterance: I think that -- that is not what your average everyday American cares about. That's what I think. I think they care about what their tax rate is. I think they care about, did they get their job back or keep the job they had. And if they did, did their wages go up? That's what I think -- you go back to the Bernie Sanders piece how he sell all these books. How do you think people have money to buy all his books? They got their taxes reduced.

utterances.speaker: RICH
utterances.utterance: Whether they know that or not, that's what happened. And so, you know, I grew up in a double wide trailer in Texas, nothing fancy, and I see all these stuff going on and I know that's how the multitude of Americans actually feel. They don't care about this report. This just a media thing that none of us really care about honestly.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Jesse, you actually keep your hair in a double wide trailer.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: My hair is about as high as Colorado, isn't it?

utterances.speaker: RICH
utterances.utterance: Higher the hair, closer to God.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: That's right.

utterances.speaker: BRAZILE
utterances.utterance: But it's all legally your hair.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Yes, all legal. That's all legal. Not edible, though.

utterances.speaker: RICH
utterances.utterance: I think we should let a good Nashville girl run their fingers through your hair before the show is over.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: All right.

utterances.speaker: RICH
utterances.utterance: Do we have any volunteers? Any volunteers? Come on down.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: I think that violates some human resources law. You're going to end up getting sued.

utterances.speaker: RICH
utterances.utterance: Not in Nashville.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: Well, here's what I think. This report when it comes out on Thursday, you will have breathless reporting. I find it very hard to believe that he wasn't being truthful. And so, now the media has built it up that he is a liar? I find that -- I think that they're going to have egg on their face again.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: All right. Donna, wipe the egg off in the break, all right? We'll be right back. We have a lot more coming up live from Nashville, including checking out some of the top spots on John Rich party bus. But first, President Trump says he's ready to send illegal immigrants to sanctuary cities.

utterances.speaker: BRAZILE
utterances.utterance: Welcome back to "The Five" live from Nashville. President Trump is attacking Democrats while he stands firm on his plans to send migrants to sanctuary cities.

utterances.speaker: PRESIDENT DONALD TRUMP
utterances.utterance: It would be a lot easier if Congress would get together and the Democrats would agree to get rid of these loopholes, these horrible and foolish loopholes, the catch and release, and chain migration, and visa lottery.

utterances.speaker: BRAZILE
utterances.utterance: You know, I think the president is on shaky legal ground. Some in his administration believe it as well. And you know members of Congress will oppose it. But some of the migrant, mayors and others are saying bring it on, Mr. President. What's your view, brother?

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: I take it you're referring to me, not Dana.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: This reminds me of when you -- when somebody brags about their gym routine, what they can lift, what they can squat, and then you asked them to help you move and suddenly they have a bad back.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Greg, I have a bad back.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: There you have a bad back. But that's the liberal mayor. That's De Blasio saying, oh, this is -- wait, you want the migrants to come here and now you don't. Why is it, because of Trump. Put your money where your mouth is. It's only an opinion if you don't -- it's not an opinion if there's no practical belief behind it.

utterances.speaker: BRAZILE
utterances.utterance: These individuals have been caught at the border. There are not enough beds. And what the president is proposing out of retaliation because the Democrats are not going along with his plan, is to ship them off to cities, it's costly, on buses, vans, planes, airplanes, your private jet --

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: You don't want to have them walk.

utterances.speaker: BRAZILE
utterances.utterance: But this is the point. The point is, is that why not go to Congress if this is what the president believes?

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Any -- that begins with why not go to Congress never end well.

utterances.speaker: BRAZILE
utterances.utterance: Well, the president had Republicans for two years and nothing happens.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Donna, Democrats do with they usually do. They got caught with their pants down.

utterances.speaker: BRAZILE
utterances.utterance: Really?

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Donald Trump called their bluff and now they're shaking in their boots. This is what happens. For the last two years, Democrats said there's no crisis. We don't need walls. We need bridges. The caravan is just a bunch of women and children. We need workers. Trump is trying to stir up hate and resentment. Then all of a sudden Trump said, OK, you take him then. And then what happened. They totally changed their rhetoric when they've got smacked in the face by reality. If that happened and they sent 30,000 refugees to midtown Manhattan, what do you think Bill de Blasio would do. He'd have a humanitarian crisis. He'd have a political crisis. He can't even handle a snow storm.

utterances.speaker: BRAZILE
utterances.utterance: But it seems as though the President is trying to throw everything against the wall to see what sticks and this is not going to stick.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: I think you know we talked a little bit about this yesterday. He's changing the debate, right. So, he hasn't been able to achieve some of the things to Congress because of Greg says that doesn't - that's not working well. I don't see why the Democrats instead of saying, well that's just - we can't have that. And now their claim for an investigation.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Good impression.

utterances.speaker: BRAZILE
utterances.utterance: Yes.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: OK. Why don't they just flip the script and say and as President said, well you know that's never going to happen and sorry that you can't achieve anything and you're the worst deal maker ever. OK, whatever. And just sit back instead they have to make such a big deal about it and call for an investigation that--

utterances.speaker: BRAZILE
utterances.utterance: That's because the President continue - John you have a point.

utterances.speaker: RICH
utterances.utterance: Well. I was just going to say if you really care about the folks that are piling up on the border, do you want them to stay in an overcrowded border town or do you want to send them to Northern California in the upper level districts and zip codes of that state where they can really have a nice meal, nice place to--

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: I heard the wine in San Francisco is really good.

utterances.speaker: BRAZILE
utterances.utterance: Just so you all know sanctuary cities are all over the country not just in big cities, but also small and rural communities. No, it is true. I've studied this issue. The sanctuary cities are all across America. But you know what, I want to say this, I think it's time that Congress and the President get together and try to solve this immigration crisis.

utterances.speaker: RICH
utterances.utterance: I agree with this.

utterances.speaker: BRAZILE
utterances.utterance: All right. Now, by the way, Kathie Lee Gifford is here. Live here at Nashville. Kathie Lee, come on over.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: I think that song is about gambling. I'm not sure. Welcome back to The Five for Nashville. That's the Joe Denim band playing live music. Joining us now is TV legend. Don't you hate that? Call you a legend.

utterances.speaker: KATHIE LEE GIFFORD, TELEVISION HOST
utterances.utterance: I hate that. You're almost dead.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: You're not there though.

utterances.speaker: GIFFORD
utterances.utterance: No.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: You've got more lives than cats. Let's put it that way. I miss you.

utterances.speaker: GIFFORD
utterances.utterance: I miss you too buddy.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: What have you been up to?

utterances.speaker: GIFFORD
utterances.utterance: Not much.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: You used to talk a lot.

utterances.speaker: GIFFORD
utterances.utterance: Mommy again.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: Congratulations.

utterances.speaker: GIFFORD
utterances.utterance: I know. I'm thrilled about that. I knew that was coming. I just didn't know when it was going to happen.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: It's sort of a long walk up to the - because you announced quite a while ago that you were going to leave The Today Show. What's it been like in the last, was it 10 days or so?

utterances.speaker: GIFFORD
utterances.utterance: I think so I've lost - I mean--

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: You're not counting.

utterances.speaker: GIFFORD
utterances.utterance: I'm not counting because I had given my notice two years before because I knew it was time. You know you've run out of tick tock in life and there are things I wanted to do and been dying to do, and you've just got to make time for certain things. And I've been so blessed to be there for 11 years and make the friendships that I had. But it was time.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: You're like a block away from us, but we never stop by - you never stop by. We're like down the street from you.

utterances.speaker: GIFFORD
utterances.utterance: Like NBC lets me go over to Fox. Come on.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: But now you're free.

utterances.speaker: GIFFORD
utterances.utterance: Now I'm free, I can go anywhere. I'm going to do some porn. Right. I think why not.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: I thought you would say, documentary.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: I think that might be first for Fox News. Kathie Lee Gifford and she is doing porn. For News. If that doesn't make it into the primetime.

utterances.speaker: GIFFORD
utterances.utterance: It just makes me happy to say that. I don't know why. It's so ridiculous. I love it.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Why is it ridiculous.

utterances.speaker: GIFFORD
utterances.utterance: Well, because there actually are some really strange sick people out there that actually like--

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Talking about Jesse by the way.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Thank you.

utterances.speaker: BRAZILE
utterances.utterance: Can I ask you a question? You have written so many remarkable books including party animals and I have - my godson is three years old and I understand you are about to write another book or release a book, right?

utterances.speaker: GIFFORD
utterances.utterance: No, I have two books out right now. One's called the Rock the road and the Rabbi. It's about my rabbinical trips to Israel.

utterances.speaker: BRAZILE
utterances.utterance: Great.

utterances.speaker: GIFFORD
utterances.utterance: And then I have a little book for children called The Gift that I Can Give which I'll give you one of those for your--

utterances.speaker: BRAZILE
utterances.utterance: Thank you.

utterances.speaker: GIFFORD
utterances.utterance: I love to write. I have a little short film out right now called The God Who Sees. Look at how I segue from porn to The God Who Sees.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: I know, and children's books.

utterances.speaker: GIFFORD
utterances.utterance: And children's books.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: You've won our attention.

utterances.speaker: GIFFORD
utterances.utterance: I know. It's a song that I wrote with an incredible artist named Nicole C. Mullen and we didn't know where it was going to take us. It's 11.5 minutes. It tells the story. There is Nicole. Tells the story of Hagar into Ruth into David and their wilderness experiences. We shot it in Israel about a month ago. And then to Mary Magdalene, the empty tomb in Jerusalem. But it's having a powerful effect on people because it really - that's the first time that God is mentioned, a name for him in the Bible. And so, God who sees and you think about it. Hagar look at it, everybody thinks the Bible is like this 5,000-year-old dusty book that has no relevance. Hagar was sex trafficked. Hagar was a slave. Hagar was a single mother. Ruth was an immigrant and she was a widow who'd felt like she had no future left for her. Then you go to David, who's supposed to be the king, he's been anointed, but now he's hiding it and he's probably - if he had drugs back then he'd be on every - all the drugs everybody because he's terrified in fear and in despair. And then Mary Magdalene had mental illness.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Kathie Lee. Speaking of God, how is Regis doing?

utterances.speaker: GIFFORD
utterances.utterance: Regis is good. Regis is really good. He lives in California now in the winter time, so I don't see him much unless I'm in LA. But he comes back to Connecticut and we hang out a lot in the summertime. We're still so close.

utterances.speaker: RICH
utterances.utterance: I have to get a question in. How do you like Nashville so far?

utterances.speaker: GIFFORD
utterances.utterance: You know how I - the first place I came, the first party I went to is your house.

utterances.speaker: RICH
utterances.utterance: Yes, ma'am.

utterances.speaker: BRAZILE
utterances.utterance: I wasn't invited.

utterances.speaker: RICH
utterances.utterance: You've got to go.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: What's it like to have Kathie Lee in Nashville.

utterances.speaker: RICH
utterances.utterance: It was unbelievable. You know we love you because you're so genuine and you're a real country girl and this town has all the fireworks of entertainment, everything else, but it's a down to earth country. Right here in the middle of the country too.

utterances.speaker: GIFFORD
utterances.utterance: You know what I love so much about it. What I do not miss about the northeast is the arrogance of it and--

utterances.speaker: RICH
utterances.utterance: People like Greg.

utterances.speaker: GIFFORD
utterances.utterance: No, I've got great friends up there too. I don't mean this as a blanket statement, but as a culture. It's a glitchy gotcha kind of a culture and after 35 years of it, I just said you know what I want to hang out with people that love God, love my wine, love music, love our country.

utterances.speaker: RICH
utterances.utterance: Dr. Pepper.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Still making wine?

utterances.speaker: GIFFORD
utterances.utterance: You bring the--

utterances.speaker: RICH
utterances.utterance: Bingo.

utterances.speaker: GIFFORD
utterances.utterance: Whiskey.

utterances.speaker: RICH
utterances.utterance: I'll bring the wine.

utterances.speaker: GIFFORD
utterances.utterance: That's right.

utterances.speaker: RICH
utterances.utterance: I mean horse about Nashville time.

utterances.speaker: GIFFORD
utterances.utterance: There you go.

utterances.speaker: RICH
utterances.utterance: Let's get this going right now.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: What is happening here. All right.

utterances.speaker: RICH
utterances.utterance: We're having a moment, Greg. We're having a moment.

utterances.speaker: GIFFORD
utterances.utterance: This is a big - I'm done.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: We're going to do this again you know.

utterances.speaker: GIFFORD
utterances.utterance: OK. Where?

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: I don't know later tonight.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Greg, she's joking about the porn career.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: You mentioned support in one segment. Up next.

utterances.speaker: GIFFORD
utterances.utterance: How is your wife by the wife.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
